FDIC Says Sheila Bair Will Step Down as Body’s Chairman Effective July 8

-- B y   G r e g o r y   M o t t
-- 
2011-05-09T18:50:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/fdic-says-sheila-bair-will-step-down-as-body-s-chairman-effective-july-8.html
The  Federal Deposit Insurance
Corporation  said  Sheila Bair ’s official departure as chairman of
the agency will be effective July 8.  “Consistent with previous public statements, Chairman Bair
has announced her intention to depart the agency following the
expiration of her term,” The FDIC said today in a statement.
Bair will lead her final meeting as chairman during the first
week of July, the agency said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gregory Mott in Washington at 
